        <h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <h3 id="is-sponsored-content-the-same-as-native-advertising">Is sponsored content the same as native advertising?</h3>
        <p>They're closely related. <a href="/glossary/native-advertising/">Native advertising</a> is the broader category. Ads that match the platform's format. Sponsored content is a type of native ad that specifically focuses on content (articles, posts, videos) rather than display units.</p>
        <h3 id="does-sponsored-content-need-to-be-labeled">Does sponsored content need to be labeled?</h3>
        <p>Yes. The FTC requires clear disclosure of paid partnerships. Platforms add their own labels ("Sponsored," "Promoted"), and creators must use tags like #ad or "Paid partnership with." Transparency is both legally required and trust-building.</p>
        <h3 id="what-makes-sponsored-content-effective">What makes sponsored content effective?</h3>
        <p>Value first, promotion second. The best sponsored content teaches something, tells a story, or solves a problem. If readers would engage with it even without the sponsorship, you've done it right.</p>
